1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual saliency prediction for HDR videos, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with HDR video content, which is a type of multimedia content. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as the paper deals with visual attention models for HDR videos, which is related to graphics and image processing. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses an eye-tracking experiment, which is related to human-computer interaction. 
5. cs.MM (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a learning-based visual saliency fusion method, which involves machine learning techniques.
